3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses a deep learning model to solve the PnP problem, which falls under the category of machine learning. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The use of deep learning to solve a challenging problem in computer vision and robotics can be considered as an application of artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics) - The PnP problem is also relevant in computer graphics, particularly in the context of camera calibration and pose estimation.
